Group%20Captain%20Prasanth%20Balakrishnan%20Nair%20as%20a%20designated%20astronaut%20who%20will%20become%20part%20of%20Ax-4%20should%20Mr%20Shukla%20be%20unable%20to%20fly.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20part%20of%20an%20agreement%20between%20NASA%20and%20the%20Indian%20Space%20Research%20Organisation%20(ISRO)%2C%20India%20bought%20a%20seat%20for%20its%20astronaut%20on%20the%20upcoming%20mission%20to%20space%20by%20Axiom%20Space%20Inc%2C%20a%20Houston-based%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAx-4%2C%20the%20fourth%20private%20astronaut%20mission%20to%20the%20ISS%2C%20is%20targeted%20to%20launch%20from%20the%20Kennedy%20Space%20Center%20in%20Florida.%20It%20will%20launch%20aboard%20a%20SpaceX%20Dragon%20spacecraft%20hoisted%20by%20the%20Falcon-9%20rocket%2C%20which%20will%20fly%20them%20to%20the%20space%20station.%20Once%20docked%2C%20the%20astronauts%20are%20scheduled%20to%20spend%20up%20to%2014%20days%20aboard%20the%20orbiting%20laboratory%2C%20conducting%20a%20mission%20comprised%20of%20science%2C%20outreach%20and%20commercial%20activities.%20The%20private%20mission%20also%20carries%20the%20first%20astronauts%20from%20Poland%20and%20Hungary%20to%20stay%20aboard%20the%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20NASA%2C%20the%20first%20private%20astronaut%20mission%20to%20the%20station%20Axiom%20Mission%201%20lifted%20off%20in%20April%202022%20for%20a%2017-day%20mission%20aboard%20the%20orbiting%20laboratory.%20The%20second%20private%20astronaut%20mission%20to%20the%20station%20Axiom%20Mission%202%20launched%20in%20May%202023%20with%20four%20private%20astronauts%20who%20spent%20eight%20days%20in%20orbit.%20The%20most%20recent%20private%20astronaut%20mission%20Axiom%20Mission%203%20launched%20in%20January%202024%2C%20with%20the%20crew%20spending%2018%20days%20at%20the%20space%20station.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAx-4's%20likely%20launch%20in%20May%20will%20come%20months%20after%20Indian-origin%20NASA%20astronaut%20Sunita%20Williams%20returned%20to%20Earth%20after%20spend