hina.%20He%20insists%20this%20will%20revitalise%20domestic%20manufacturing%2C%20though%20it%20risks%20a%20global%20trade%20war.%20Trump%20expressed%20frustration%20with%20international%20trade%20practices%2C%20vowing%20to%20boost%20jobs%20and%20industry%20within%20the%20US%20while%20portraying%20his%20measures%20as%20a%20necessary%20resistance%20against%20foreign%20exploitation.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftheyre-ripping-us-off-they-understood-it-key-takeaways-from-trumps-tariff-speech%2Farticleshow%2F119924933.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftheyre-ripping-us-off-they-understood-it-key-takeaways-from-trumps-tariff-speech%2Famp_articleshow%2F119924933.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ftheyre-ripping-us-off-they-understood-it-key-takeaways-from-trumps-tariff-speech%2Famp_articleshow%2F119924933.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Trump%20Tariffs%20Q%26amp%3BA%3A%20How%20Soon%20Will%20Prices%20Rise%2C%20Are%20Other%20Countries%20Taxing%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EAfter%20weeks%20of%20anticipation%20and%20speculation%2C%20President%20Donald%20Trump%20followed%20through%20on%20his%20tariff%20threats%20by%20declaring%20on%20Wednesday%20a%2010%25%20baseline%20tax%20on%20imports%20from%20all%20countries%20and%20higher%20tariff%20rates%20on%20dozens%20of%20nations%20that%20run%20trade%20surpluses%20with%20the%20United%20States.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20announcing%20what%20he%20has%20called%20reciprocal%20tariffs%2C%20Trump%20was%20fulfilling%20a%20key%20campaign%20promise%20by%20raising%20US%20taxes%20on%20foreign%20goods%20to%20narrow%20the%20gap%20with%20the%20tariffs%20the%20White%20House%20says%20other%20countries%20unfairly%20impose%20on%20US%20products.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump's%20higher%20rates%20would%20hit%20foreign%20entities%20that%20sell%20more%20goods%20to%20the%20United%20States%20than%20they%20buy.%20But%20economists%20don't%20share%20Trump's%20enthusiasm%20for%20tariffs%20since%20they're%20a%20tax%20on%20importers%20that%20usually%20get%20passed%20on%20to%20consumers.%20It's%20possible%2C%20however%2C%20that%20the%20reciprocal%20tariffs%20could%20bring%20other%20countries%20to%20the%20table%20and%20get%20them%20to%20lower%20their%20own%20import%20taxes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Associated%20Press%20asked%20for%20your%20questions%20about%20reciprocal%20tariffs.%20Here%20are%20a%20few%20of%20them%2C%20along%20with%20our%20answers%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDo%20US-collected%20tariffs%20go%20into%20the%20General%20Revenue%20Fund%3F%20Can%20Trump%20withdraw%20money%20from%20that%20fund%20without%20oversight%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETariffs%20are%20taxes%20on%20imports%2C%20collected%20when%20foreign%20goods%20cross%20the%20US%20border%20by%20the%20Customs%20and%20Border%20Protection%20agency.%20The%20money%20-%20about%20%2480%20billion%20last%20year%20-%20goes%20to%20the%20US%20Treasury%20to%20help%20pay%20the%20federal%20government's%20expenses.%20Congress%20has%20authority%20to%20say%20how%20the%20money%20will%20be%20spent.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20-%20largely%20supported%20by%20Republican%20lawmakers%20who%20control%20the%20US%20Senate%20and%20House%20of%20Representatives%20-%20wants%20to%20use%20increased%20tariff%20revenue%20to%20finance%20tax%20cuts%20that%20analysts%20say%20would%20disproportionately%20benefit%20the%20wealthy.%20Specifically%2C%20they%20want%20to%20extend%20tax%20cuts%20passed%20in%20Trump's%20first%20term%20and%20largely%20set%20to%20expire%20at%20the%20end%20of%202025.%20The%20Tax%20Foundation%2C%20a%20nonpartisan%20think%20tank%20in%20Washington%2C%20has%20found%20that%20extending%20Trump's%20tax%20cuts%20would%20reduce%20federal%20revenue%20by%20%244.5%20trillion%20from%202025%20to%202034.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETrump%20wants%20higher%20tariffs%20to%20help%20offset%20the%20lower%20tax%20collections.%20Another%20think%20tank%2C%20the%20Tax%20Policy%20Center%2C%20has%20said%20that%20extending%20the%202017%20tax%20cuts%20would%20deliver%20continued%20tax%20relief%20to%20Americans%20at%20all%20income%20levels%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20higher-income%20households%20would%20receive%20a%20larger%20benefit.''%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHow%20soon%20will%20prices%20rise%20as%20a%20result%20of%20the%20tariff%20policy%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20depends%20on%20how%20businesses%20both%20in%20the%20United%20States%20and%20overseas%20respond%2C%20but%20consumers%20could%20see%20overall%20prices%20rising%20within%20a%20month%20or%20two%20of%20tariffs%20being%20imposed.%20For%20some%20products%2C%20such%20as%20produce%20from%20Mexico%2C%20prices%20could%20rise%20much%20more%20quickly%20after%20the%20tariffs%20take%20effect.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20US%20retailers%20and%20other%20importers%20may%20eat%20part%20of%20the%20cost%20of%20the%20tariff%2C%20and%20overseas%20exporters%20may%20reduce%20their%20prices%20to%20offset%20the%20extra%20duties.%20But%20for%20many%20businesses%2C%20the%20tariffs%20Trump%20announced%20Wednesday%20-%20such%20as%2020%25%20on%20imports%20from%20Europe%20-%20will%20be%20too%20large%20to%20swallow%20on%20their%20own.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECompanies%20may%20also%20use%20the%20tariffs%20as%20an%20excuse%20to%20raise%20prices.%20When%20Trump%20slapped%20duties%20on%20washing%20machines%20in%202018%2C%20studies%20later%20showed%20that%20retailers%20raised%20prices%20on%20both%20washers%20and%20dryers%2C%20even%20though%20there%20were%20no%20new%20duties%20on%20dryers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20question%20in%20the%20coming%20months%20is%20whether%20something%20similar%20will%20happen%20again.%20Economists%20worry%20that%20consumers%2C%20having%20just%20lived%20through%20the%20biggest%20inflationary%20spike%20in%20four%20decades%2C%20are%20more%20accustomed%20to%20rising%20prices%20than%20they%20were%20before%20the%20pandemic.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20there%20are%20also%20signs%20that%20Americans%2C%20put%20off%20by%20the%20rise%20in%20the%20cost%20of%20living%2C%20are%20less%20willing%20to%20accept%20price%20increases%20and%20will%20simply%20cut%20back%20on%20their%20purchases.%20That%20could%20discourage%20businesses%20from%20raising%20prices%20by%20much.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20is%20the%20limit%20of%20the%20executive%20branch's%20power%20to%20implement%20tariffs%3F%20Does%20Congress%20not%20play%20any%20role%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Constitution%20grants%20the%20power%20to%20set%20tariffs%20to%20Congress.%20But%20over%20the%20years%2C%20Congress%20has%20delegated%20those%20powers%20to%20the%20president%20through%20several%20different%20laws.%20Those%20laws%20specify%20the%20circumstances%20under%20which%20the%20White%20House%20can%20impose%20tariffs%2C%20which%20are%20typically%20limited%20to%20cases%20where%20imports%20threaten%20national%20security%20or%20are%20severely%20harming%20a%20specific%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20presidents%20generally%20imposed%20tariffs%20only%20after%20carrying%20out%20public%20hearings%20to%20determine%20if%20certain%20imports%20met%20those%20criteria.%20Trump%20followed%20those%20steps%20when%20imposing%20tariffs%20in%20his%20first%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20second%20term%2C%20however%2C%20Trump%20has%20sought%20to%20use%20emergency%20powers%20set%20out%20in%20a%201977%20law%20to%20impose%20tariffs%20in%20a%20more%20ad%20hoc%20fashion.%20Trump%20has%20said%2C%20for%20example%2C%20that%20fentanyl%20flowing%20in%20from%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20constitute%20a%20national%20emergency%20and%20has%20used%20that%20pretext%20to%20impose%2025%25%20duties%20on%20goods%20from%20both%20countries.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECongress%20can%20seek%20to%20cancel%20an%20emergency%20that%20a%20president%20declares%2C%20and%20Sen.%20Tim%20Kaine%2C%20a%20Democrat%20from%20Virginia%2C%20has%20proposed%20to%20do%20just%20that%20regarding%20Canada.%20That%20legislation%20could%20pass%20the%20Senate%20but%20would%20likely%20die%20in%20the%20House.%20Other%20bills%20in%20Congress%20that%20would%20also%20limit%20the%20president's%20authority%20to%20set%20tariffs%20face%20tough%20odds%20for%20passage%20as%20well.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhat%20tariffs%20are%20other%20countries%20charging%20on%20US%20goods%3F%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUS%20tariffs%20are%20generally%20lower%20than%20those%20charged%20by%20other%20countries.%20The%20average%20US%20tariff%2C%20weighted%20to%20reflect%20goods%20that%20are%20actually%20traded%2C%20is%20just%202.2%25%20for%20the%20United%20States%2C%20versus%20the%20European%20Union's%202.7%25%2C%20China's%203%25%20and%20India's%2012%25%2C%20according%20to%20the%20World%20Trade%20Organization.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOther%20countries%20also%20tend%20to%20do%20more%20than%20the%20United%20States%20to%20protect%20their%20farmers%20with%20high%20tariffs.%20The%20US%20trade-weighted%20tariff%20on%20farm%20goods%2C%20for%20example%2C%20is%204%25%2C%20compared%20to%20the%20EU's%208.4%25%2C%20Japan's%2012.6%25%2C%20China's%2013.1%25%20and%20India's%2065%25.%20(The%20WTO%20numbers%20don't%20count%20Trump's%20recent%20flurry%20of%20import%20taxes%20or%20tariffs%20between%20countries%20that%20have%20entered%20into%20their%20own%20free%20trade%20agreements%2C%20such%20as%20the%20US-Mexico-Canada%20Agreement%20that%20allows%20many%20goods%20to%20cross%20North%20American%20borders%20duty-free.)%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYet%20the%20Trump%20administration%20has%20used%20its%20own%20calculations%20to%20come%20up%20with%20far%20greater%20tariffs%20that%20they%20say%20other%20economies%20impose%20on%20the%20US%20For%20example%2C%20the%20White%20House%20said%20Wednesday%20that%20the%20European%20Union's%20effective%20tariffs%20on%20the%20US%20equal%2039%25%2C%20far%20higher%20than%20the%20WTO's%20numbers.%20It%20says%20China's%20equal%2067%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPrevious%20US%20administrations%20agreed%20to%20the%20tariffs%20that%20Trump%20now%20calls%20unjust.%20They%20were%20the%20result%20of%20a%20long%20negotiation%20between%201986%20to%201994%20-%20the%20so-called%20Uruguay%20Round%20-%20that%20ended%20in%20a%20trade%20pact%20signed%20by%20123%20countries%20and%20has%20formed%20the%20basis%20of%20the%20global%20trading%20system%20for%20nearly%20four%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743646620000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-04%2Fejekunq_trump-tariff_625x300_03_April_25.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Ftrump-tariffs-q-a-how-soon-will-prices-rise-are-other-countries-taxing-us-8074223%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22President%20Donald%20Trump%20followed%20through%20on%20his%20tariff%20threats%20by%20declaring%20a%2010%25%20baseline%20tax%20on%20imports%20from%20all%20countries%20and%20higher%20tariff%20rates%20on%20dozens%20of%20nations%20that%20run%20trade%20surpluses%20with%20the%20United%20States.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20is%20'talented%20guy'%20Elon%20Musk%20stepping%20down%20as%20DOGE%20chief%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743646578000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-119925268%2Cimgsize-20772.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fwhy-is-talented-guy-elon-musk-stepping-down-as-doge-chief%2Farticleshow%2F119925123.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2