%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EPresident%20Donald%20Trump's%20latest%20round%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fdonald-trump-mexico-canada-tariffs-economic-uncertainty-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20two%20surprising%20omissions%3A%20Mexico%20and%20Canada.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20countries%2C%20including%20China%2C%20were%20slapped%20with%20large%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-tariffs-plan-deadline-trade-policies-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereciprocal%20tariffs%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20Wednesday.%20After%20Trump's%20announcement%2C%20CNBC%20reported%20that%20Chinese%20goods%20could%20receive%20a%2054%25%20tariff%20when%20combining%20the%20new%20tariffs%20(34%25)%20with%20ones%20that%20have%20been%20previously%20announced.%20European%20Union%20goods%20will%20be%20subject%20to%20a%20new%2020%25%20tariff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20White%20House%2C%20this%20doesn't%20mean%20the%20US's%20neighbors%20are%20off%20scot-free.%20Pre-existing%2025%25%20tariffs%20on%20most%20Mexican%20and%20Canadian%20goods%20will%20remain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2282dfdf18-7cfc-48ff-b08c-0ba2ae52dfd7%5C%22%3EUSMCA%20and%20Trump's%20previous%20tariffs%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EUnder%20Trump's%20previous%20order%2C%20a%2025%25%20tariff%20was%20applied%20to%20all%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fretailers-small-businesses-react-trump-trade-tariffs-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EMexican%20and%20Canadian%20goods%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20are%20not%20compliant%20with%20the%20United%20States-Mexico-Canada%20Agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20White%20House%20has%20said%20the%20tariffs%20are%20necessary%20because%20the%20two%20countries%20are%20not%20doing%20enough%20to%20stop%20illegal%20immigration%20and%20the%20smuggling%20of%20fentanyl%20into%20the%20United%20States%20from%20the%20northern%20and%20southern%20borders.%20Leaders%20of%20both%20countries%20have%20disputed%20this%20claim.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20USMCA%20trade%20deal%2C%20which%20replaced%20the%20North%20American%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%20in%202020%2C%20maintains%20NAFTA's%20zero-tariff%20treatment%20for%20most%20agricultural%20products%2C%20textiles%2C%20apparel%2C%20and%20other%20goods%20that%20meet%20the%20trade%20agreement's%20rules%20of%20origin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENon-compliant%20energy%20and%20potash%20from%20the%20bordering%20nations%20remain%20subject%20to%20a%2010%25%20tariff%3B%20the%20latter%20was%20viewed%20as%20the%20White%20House%20bowing%20to%20pressure%20from%20the%20farm%20industry%20worried%20about%20a%20key%20ingredient%20in%20fertilizers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChris%20Tang%2C%20a%20UCLA%20professor%20and%20expert%20in%20global%20supply%20chain%20management%20and%20the%20impact%20of%20regulatory%20policies%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20the%20Trump%20administration's%20choice%20to%20leave%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20off%20the%20tariffs%20list%20on%20Wednesday%20may%20be%20a%20symbol%20that%20the%20president%20recognizes%20the%20neighboring%20nations'%20significance%20to%20the%20US%20economy%20%E2%80%94%20but%20it's%20also%20likely%20a%20negotiation%20tactic.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSo%2C%20for%20example%2C%20right%20now%2C%20the%20products%20that%20comply%20with%20the%20USMCA%20are%20still%20tariff-free%2C%26quot%3B%20Tang%20said.%20%26quot%3BBut%20that's%20temporary.%20Trump%20has%20said%2C%20'Well%2C%20that%20may%20adjust.'%20And%20that%20gives%20him%20still%20some%20wiggle%20room%20to%20negotiate.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20Trump's%20prior%20order%20were%20terminated%2C%20a%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20White%20House%20told%20Business%20Insider%20all%20non-USMCA%20compliant%20goods%20would%20be%20reduced%20to%20a%2012%25%20tariff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMargaret%20Kidd%2C%20an%20instructional%20associate%20professor%20of%20supply%20chain%20and%20logistics%20technology%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Houston%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%2C%20%26quot%3BIt's%20not%20in%20our%20best%20interest%20for%20the%20United%20States%20to%20alienate%20our%20two%20closest%20trading%20partners.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EShe%20added%20that%20there%20was%20about%20%24945%20billion%20in%20trade%20between%20Mexico%20and%20the%20US%20in%202024%2C%20with%20most%20of%20the%20products%20exchanged%20flowing%20through%20Texas.%20The%20tariffs%20on%20the%20southern%20country%2C%20she%20said%2C%20have%20an%20outsized%20effect%20on%20the%20border%20states%2C%20which%20rely%20on%20the%20local%20economy%20built%20around%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20all%20intermingled%2C%26quot%3B%20Kidd%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETang%20said%20he's%20hopeful%20that%20the%20omission%20of%20Canada%20and%20Mexico%20from%20Wednesday's%20tariffs%20could%20act%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20olive%20branch%20with%20the%20nation's%20allies%20to%20soothe%20the%20trade%20tensions%20that%20have%20increased%20since%20Trump%20took%20office.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BReally%2C%20our%20economies%20are%20interlinked%2C%26quot%3B%20Tang%20said.%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20hopefully%2C%20they%20can%20really%20sit%20down%20and%20work%20it%20out%20because%20these%20are%20our%20allies%2C%20our%20neighbors%20%E2%80%94%20this%20is%20very%20important.%20So%20I%20hope%20there%20is%20a%20possibility%20that%20these%20three%20countries%20can%20work%20together.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-canada-mexico-missing-from-donald-trump-reciprocal-tariff-chart-2025-4%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1743645744000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67edc24869253ccddf9b176d%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwhy-canada-mexico-missing-from-donald-trump-reciprocal-tariff-chart-2025-4%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Donald%20Trump's%20latest%20round%20of%20tariffs%20had%20two%20notabl