larity.%20Business%20Insider%20has%20verified%20his%20employment%20and%20visa%20history.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20I%20completed%20my%20bachelor's%20in%20computer%20science%20in%20India%2C%20a%20series%20of%20internships%20and%20connections%20led%20me%20to%20a%20role%20at%20a%20very%20early-stage%20venture%20capital%20firm.%20I%20loved%20the%20job%20and%20the%20research%20it%20involved.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESeven%20months%20into%20working%20at%20the%20firm%2C%20I%20wanted%20the%20exposure%20of%20living%20and%20working%20abroad.%20I%20got%20into%20a%20business%20analytics%20master's%20program%20at%20Columbia%20University%20and%20moved%20to%20New%20York%20City%20in%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERight%20off%20the%20bat%2C%20I%20figured%20out%20that%20venture%20was%20not%20a%20typical%20career%20path%20for%20international%20students%2C%20including%20MBA%20and%20business%20majors%2C%20for%20one%20main%20reason%3A%20visa%20sponsorship%20issues.%20I%20interned%20at%20two%20places%20in%20the%20summer%2C%20and%20both%20said%20they%20wouldn't%20be%20able%20to%20sponsor%20my%20long-term%20visa%2C%20even%20though%20they%20liked%20my%20performance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20started%20researching%20the%20job%20market%20after%20graduation%2C%20I%20could%20not%20find%20a%20single%20person%20in%20the%20industry%20who%20was%20an%20immigrant%2C%20which%20was%20really%20demotivating.%20But%20I%20was%20convinced%20that%20I%20wanted%20to%20work%20in%20healthcare%20or%20climate%20tech%20and%20decided%20to%20keep%20going.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20Science-Technology-Engineering-Math%20graduate%2C%20I%20am%20allowed%20a%20three-year%20work%20permit%20called%20the%20Optional%20Practical%20Training%20visa.%20It's%20seen%20as%20a%20pathway%20to%20securing%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-bros-debating-maga-fans-over-h-1b-visas-2024-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cu%3EH-1B%20%E2%80%94%20a%20visa%20for%20highly%20ski