es%20precedence%20over%20elected%20officials'%20right%20to%20know%20information%20pertaining%20to%20national%20security.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20Meta%20spokesperson%20told%20BI%20that%20the%20company%20was%20%26quot%3Bnot%20intending%20to%20stand%20in%20the%20way%20of%20her%20exercising%20her%20rights.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20added%20that%20the%20company%20did%20not%20operate%20its%20services%20in%20China.%20%26quot%3BIt%20is%20no%20secret%20we%20were%20once%20interested%20in%20doing%20so%20as%20part%20of%20Facebook's%20effort%20to%20connect%20the%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%20%26quot%3BThis%20was%20widely%20reported%20beginning%20a%20decade%20ago.%20We%20ultimately%20opted%20not%20to%20go%20through%20with%20the%20ideas%20we'd%20explored%2C%20which%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20announced%20in%202019.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Senate's%20Permanent%20Subcommittee%20on%20Investigations%2C%20chaired%20by%20Republican%20Sen.%20Ron%20Johnson%20and%20joined%20by%20Democratic%20Sen.%20Richard%20Blumenthal%20and%20Republican%20Hawley%2C%20opened%20the%20probe%20into%20Meta's%20dealings%20with%20China%20on%20April%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20committee's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hsgac.senate.gov%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2025.04.01-PSI-Letter-to-Meta-Johnson-Blumenthal-Hawley-1.pdf%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eletter%3C%2Fa%3E%20sent%20to%20Meta%20CEO%20Mark%20Zuckerberg%20on%20Tuesday%20outlines%20a%20sweeping%20request%20for%20records%20dating%20back%20to%202014.%20Lawmakers%20are%20seeking%20all%20Meta%20communications%20with%20Chinese%20government%20officials%2C%20including%20the%20Cyberspace%20Administration%20of%20China%2C%20and%20records%20on%20Meta's%20subsidiaries%20and%20partners%20in%20the%20country%2C%20among%20other%20details.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20want%20information%20about%20whether%20Llama%2C%20Meta's%20AI%20model%2C%20was%20used%20by%20the%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20or%20Chinese%20tech%20firms.%20The%20r