ption%5C%22%3EJasmine%20flowers%20sell%20for%20%E2%82%B9150%20per%20kg%20on%20regular%20days%20and%20can%20fetch%20up%20to%20%E2%82%B9300%20per%20kg%20during%20festivals.%20Traders%20collect%20the%20flowers%20directly%20from%20villages%2C%20reducing%20transportation%20costs%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJasmine%2C%20known%20locally%20as%20Chameli%2C%20Malligai%2C%20Mogra%2C%20and%20Champa%20Bela%2C%20thrives%20in%20tropical%20and%20subtropical%20climates%2C%20making%20it%20well-suited%20for%20this%20region%E2%80%99s%20dry%20conditions.%20Jasminum%20sambac%2C%20the%20botanical%20name%20for%20jasmine%2C%20is%20easy%20to%20propagate%20through%20cuttings.%20The%20fragrant%20white%20flowers%20have%20nearly%20seven%20varieties%2C%20including%20Udupi%20Malligai%2C%20which%20holds%20Geographical%20Indication%20(GI)%20status%20and%20is%20highly%20sought%20after%20in%20West%20Asian%20markets.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20farmers%20like%2040-year-old%20Subhash%20Ramchandra%20Zugare%20from%20Gathan%20Adivasi%20Pada%20in%20Khor%20village%2C%20jasmine%20offers%20multiple%20advantages%3A%20%E2%80%9CMogra%20survives%20droughts%2C%20requires%20minimal%20fertilizers%2C%20and%20has%20a%20stable%20market%20demand.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJasmine%20flowers%20sell%20for%20Rs%20150%20per%20kg%20on%20regular%20days%20and%20can%20fetch%20up%20to%20%E2%82%B9300%20per%20kg%20during%20festivals.%20Traders%20collect%20the%20flowers%20directly%20from%20villages%2C%20reducing%20transportation%20costs%20for%20farmers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20shift%20to%20mogra%20cultivation%20has%20significantly%20improved%20incomes%2C%20with%20families%20earning%20an%20additional%20Rs%207%2C000%20annually.%20Depending%20on%20the%20flowering%20season%2C%20monthly%20earnings%20range%20between%20Rs%202%2C000%20to%20Rs%203%2C000%2C%20offering%20a%20sustainable%20livelihood%20to%20these%20communities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EBeyond%20Ja